This paper is primarily concerned with the security of routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks (MANETs), which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses communication and adversary models, which are relevant to the field of network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves formal reasoning and analysis of protocols, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and software engineering (cs.SE).
